ted F.C.|Carlisle United]] || [[Brunton Park|A]]\n | [http://www.oldhamathletic.co.uk/page/NewsUpdate/0,,10337~1751558,00.html 0 \u2013 1]\n |\n | 2,509\n|}\n\n===Johnstone's Paint Trophy===\nOn 15 August 2009, the First Round draw for the [[2009\u201310 Football League Trophy]] was made on ''[[Soccer AM]]'', where Oldham was drawn against [[Football League Two|League Two]] club [[Accrington Stanley F.C.|Accrington Stanley]].<ref>{{cite news| url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/8184393.stm| title=Johnstone's Paint Trophy first round draw| work=BBC Sport| date=15 August 2009| accessdate=1 September 2009}}</ref> The Latics held a 1\u20130 lead at halftime after [[Danny Whitaker]] grabbed a goal in the 10th minute, though [[Accrington Stanley F.C.|Accrington Stanley]] came back on level terms in the 60th minute due to an [[own goal]] by Oldham defender [[Sean Gregan]]. [[Phil Edwards (footballer)|Phil Edwards]] scored the winning goal seven minutes later following a free kick, giving Accrington a 2\u20131 victory and knocking Oldham out of the competition in the First Round.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/8230394.stm| title=Oldham 1\u20132 Accrington Stanley| work=BBC Sport| date=1 September 2009| accessdate=1 September 2009}}</ref>\n\n{| border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"4\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! Date !! Round !! Opponents !! H / A !! Result<br>F \u2013 A !! Scorers !! Attendance\n|- bgcolor=\"#ffddff\"\n | 1 September 2009 || First Round || [[Accrington Stanley F.C.|Accrington Stanley]] || H\n | [http://www.oldhamathletic.co.uk/page/NewsUpdate/0,,10337~1785104,00.html 1 \u2013 2]\n | [[Danny Whitaker|Whitaker]] 10'\n | 1,619\n|}\n\n==Squad statistics==\n:<small>Accurate as of end of season</small>\n{| class=wikitable style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n !rowspan=2 valign=bottom|No.\n !rowspan=2 valign=bottom|Pos.\n !rowspan=2|Name\n !colspan=2 width=85|[[2009\u201310 Football League One|League One